@model string
@using Beis.VendorManagement.Web.Constants
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Accessibility Statement";
    var webUrl = $"https://{Model}";
}
<a class="govuk-back-link" href="@Url.RouteUrl(RouteNameConstants.HomeIndexGet)">
    Back
</a>

@section Authentication {
    <partial name="_Authentication" />
}

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Accessibility statement for Help to Grow: Vendor Management</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">This accessibility statement applies to the website: <a href="@webUrl" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">@Model</a></p>
        <p class="govuk-body">This website is run by the Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy (BEIS). We want as many people as possible to be able to use this website. For example, that means you should be able to:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>change colours, contrast levels and fonts</li>
            <li>zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
            <li>navigate most of the website using just a keyboard</li>
            <li>navigate most of the website using speech recognition software</li>
            <li>listen to most of the website using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">We've also made the website text as simple as possible to understand.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body"><a href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">AbilityNet</a> has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How accessible this website is</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">We know some parts of this website are not fully accessible:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>Some page imagery contains inappropriate alternative text values.</li>
            <li>Some page content is not identified with appropriate ARIA landmarks.</li>
            <li>Not all form fields have a correctly associated form labels.</li>
            <li>Some pages may require two-dimensional scrolling when zooming the page to 400% zoom.</li>
            <li>HTML validation errors are present which may introduce issues for users navigating with assistive technologies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Get help if you have difficulty using a computer</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">If you have difficulty using a computer, you can call or email the Assisted Digital Team.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Assisted Digital Team<br>
            Telephone: 020 7215 5000<br>
            Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm <br />
            Find out about call charges.<br>
            <a href="mailto:sme.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">sme.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Accessing information in a different format</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body"><a href="mailto:sme.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">Email</a> us if you need information on this website in a different format, such as a printed copy of any of the information contained on this website.
        <p class="govuk-body">In your email, include:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>The web address (URL) of the content</li>
            <li>Your email address and name</li>
            <li>The format you need</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">We'll consider your request and get back to you with an initial response.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Reporting accessibility problems with this website</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">We're always looking to improve the accessibility of this website. If you find any problems not listed on this page or think we're not meeting accessibility requirements, <a href="mailto:sme.helptogrow@beis.gov.uk" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">email us</a> or call 020 7215 5000.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Enforcement procedure</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the 'accessibility regulations'). If you're not happy with how we respond to your complaint, <a href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS).</a></p>

        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Technical information about this website's accessibility</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">The Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy (BEIS) is committed to making its website accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Compliance status</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">This website is partially compliant with the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1</a> AA standard, due to the non-compliances and exemptions listed below.</p>

        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Non-accessible content</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">The content listed below is non-accessible for the following reasons.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Non-compliance with the accessibility regulations</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">Some decorative imagery contains an inappropriate alternative text value. This can cause confusion to users of assistive technologies such as screen readers. This fails WCAG 2.1 success criterion 1.1.1 (Non-Decorative Imagery).</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We plan to resolve this by: 21 December 2021</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Some form inputs such as file upload, or email and password fields do not have a correctly associated label. This may cause the visual label to be missed by screen readers. This fails WCAG 2.1 success criterion 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships).</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We plan to resolve this by: 21 December 2021</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Some empty navigation elements are present on the website. This may be confusing to some screen reader users who navigate using landmarks. This fails WCAG 2.1 success criterion 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships).</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We plan to resolve this by: 21 December 2021</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Some pages contain two-dimensional scrolling which may be required to access some content. This fails WCAG 2.1 success criterion 1.4.10 (Reflow).</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We plan to resolve this by: 21 December 2021</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Some pages contain HTML validation errors which may introduce issues for users who navigate using assistive technologies. This fails WCAG 2.1 success criterion 4.1.1 (Parsing).</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We plan to resolve this by: 21 December 2021</p>

        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Preparation of this accessibility statement</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">This statement was prepared on 22/10/2021. It was last reviewed on 07/12/2021.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">This website was last tested on 20/10/2021. The test was carried out by Zoonou.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">We used this approach to deciding on a sample of pages to test <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG-EM" target="_blank" class="govuk-link">WCAG-EM.</a></p>

    </div>
</div>